{"id":690882,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Madeira_bus_crash","text":"e=\"preserve\">On 17 April 2019, a tour bus crashed in Cani\u00E7o, in the archipelago of Madeira, Portugal. The bus was carrying 56 people, mostly tourists from Germany. 29 people were killed in the crash. Of the 29 dead, all of them were German. Another 27 more were injured, including the Portuguese driver and guide.\nPortuguese Prime Minister Ant\u00F3nio Costa gave his support to German Chancellor Angela Merkel. The President of Portugal, Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa, made plans to visit the site of the crash. German foreign minister Heiko Maas went to Madeira on 18 April to help victims.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Tourist","surface_form":"tour","offset":33},{"uri":"Bus","surface_form":"bus","offset":38},{"uri":"Cani%C3%A7o","surface_form":"Cani\u00E7o","offset":53},{"uri":"Archipelago","surface_form":"archipelago","offset":68},{"uri":"Madeira","surface_form":"Madeira","offset":83},{"uri":"Portugal","surface_form":"Portugal","offset":92},{"uri":"Germany","surface_form":"Germany","offset":155},{"uri":"Germans","surface_form":"German","offset":233},{"uri":"Injury","surface_form":"injured","offset":262},{"uri":"Portuguese_people","surface_form":"Portuguese","offset":285},{"uri":"Tour_guide","surface_form":"guide","offset":307},{"uri":"Prime_Minister_of_Portugal","surface_form":"Portuguese Prime Minister","offset":314},{"uri":"Ant%C3%B3nio_Costa","surface_form":"Ant\u00F3nio Costa","offset":340},{"uri":"German_Chancellor","surface_form":"German Chancellor","offset":374},{"uri":"Angela_Merkel","surface_form":"Angela Merkel","offset":392},{"uri":"President_of_Portugal","surface_form":"President of Portugal","offset":411},{"uri":"Marcelo_Rebelo_de_Sousa","surface_form":"Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa","offset":434},{"uri":"Foreign_minister","surface_form":"foreign minister","offset":509},{"uri":"Heiko_Maas","surface_form":"Heiko Maas","offset":526}]}